On or after November 1 of each year, a license may be renewed for a 1-year term, if the licensee:
Otherwise is entitled to be licensed;
Files evidence of a surety device required under § 12-412 of this subtitle;
Pays to the Commissioner a nonrefundable renewal fee of $2,000; and
Submits to the Commissioner:
A renewal application in the form and in accordance with the process that the Commissioner requires;
A financial statement that complies with the requirements of § 12-407(b)(4) of this subtitle; and
Any other information that the Commissioner reasonably requires to determine that the renewal applicant continues to be eligible to be licensed.
